  "prompt": "What is the business model for SpaFinder.com?",
  "response": "SpaFinder was an online marketplace and booking platform for spa and wellness experiences. Their business model involved:\n\n1. Connecting consumers with spas, wellness centers, and wellness experiences\n\n2. Generating revenue through:\n- Commission from bookings made through their platform\n- Advertising from spa and wellness businesses\n- Selling gift cards and spa packages\n- Offering membership programs\n\n3. Providing services such as:\n- Online spa and wellness service bookings\n- Reviews and ratings\n- Travel and wellness destination information\n- Gift card sales\n\nThe company was acquired by Spafinder Wellness 365 and went through various ownership changes over the years. Their primary goal was to make spa and wellness experiences more accessible and easier to discover and book online.\n\nPlease note that business models can change over time, so the most current details might differ from this historical overview.",
